      "body": "\r\n**I'm submitting a ...**  (check one with \"x\")\r\n```\r\n[x] feature request\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Current behavior**\r\nCurrent implementation of AOT does not allow us to set defaultEncapsulation as compilerOptions.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nWe should be able to pass a flag, or have some type of option available in the tsconfig.json to specify the defaultEncapsulation.\r\n\r\n**What is the motivation / use case for changing the behavior?**\r\nWhen using JIT we have the option to pass compilerOptions to the bootstrapModule function like so:\r\n` platformBrowserDynamic().bootstrapModule(NGAppModule, {defaultEncapsulation: ViewEncapsulation.None});`\r\n\r\nWhen we compile the templates and use the factory with `platformBrowser().bootstrapModuleFactory()`, there is no option to specify the compilerOptions. Obviously this is the case, cause these factories are precompiled.\r\n\r\nSo because of that, having defaultEncapsulation as a tsconfig.json or a compiler option would be fantastic.\r\n\r\n**Please tell us about your environment:**\r\nWindows 10\r\n\r\n* **Angular version:** 2.0.X\r\n\r\n* **Browser:** [all]\r\n \r\n* **Language:** [all]\r\n\r\n* **Node (for AoT issues):** `node --version` =  v5.10.1\r\n"
