      "body": "**I'm submitting a feature request**\r\n\r\nI'd like to see an opt-in change tracking mechanism for forms, i.e., an improved version of ng-dirty/ng-pristine which is based upon the initial value instead of a boolean flag.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n    Initial Value = \"Hello\"\r\n    User presses 'a' => new value = \"Helloa\", field marked as ng-dirty\r\n    User presses backspace => new value = \"Hello\" == initial value, field reset to ng-pristine\r\n\r\nMaybe there is also a nice way to implement this myself, without having to write cumbersome logic in my components? E.g. some sort of interceptor which one could apply?\r\n"
