      "body": "**I'm submitting a ...**\r\n```\r\n[x ] bug report => search github for a similar issue or PR before submitting\r\n[ ] feature request\r\n[ ] support request => Please do not submit support request here, instead see https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#question\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Current behavior**\r\nBrowsers don't jump directly to the id given in the fragment of a link from outside (details see below).\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nBrowsers should jump directly to the id given in the fragment of the URL.\r\n\r\n**Minimal reproduction of the problem with instructions**\r\nI took the â€ž5 min Quickstartâ€œ and replaced the code in app.component by 2 simple divs with ids â€žsection1â€œ and â€žsection2â€œ:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\nimport { Component } from '@angular/core'; \r\n  \r\n@Component({  \r\n    selector: 'my-app',  \r\n    template:   \r\n    `<div id=\"section1\" style=\"height: 1500px; background: yellow\">Section 1</div>  \r\n     <div id=\"section2\" style=\"height: 1500px; background: orange\">Section 2</div>`  \r\n})  \r\nexport class AppComponent {}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen I paste `localhost:3000/#section2` in the address bar: \r\n- Firefox stays at the top of the page until the user hits â€žEnterâ€œ (after deselecting), \r\n- Chrome stays in each case on the top of the page, \r\n- Edge seems to go randomly to section1 or section2.\r\n\r\n**What is the motivation / use case for changing the behavior?**\r\nLinks from outside should work without special handling in the code, because one doesn't know in advance, which element of a page a user will pick to set a deep link to this element. Therefore there should be no difference, whether the 2 divs are placed in index.html (which would work, of course) or in app.component.ts (which is not working).\r\n\r\n**Please tell us about your environment:**\r\n\r\nWindows 10 (1607),\r\nVisual Studio Code, \r\nnpm, \r\ndefault Quickstart configuration without any changes (besides the 2 mentioned divs)\r\n\r\n(I heared that the same app.component file behaves correctly when part of an angular-cli project(?))\r\n\r\n* **Angular version:**\r\n2.0.2\r\n\r\n* **Browser:**\r\nsee above (\"reproduction\")\r\n \r\n* **Language:** \r\nTypeScript\r\n\r\n* **Node (for AoT issues):**\r\n6.7.0   \r\n"
